@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Gemology' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  In each game level, between 3 to 8 types of gems are randomly
placed on the board. On some levels, blocks are also added, these
are placed following a certain pattern and serve no other purpose
than to complicate the game a little.

  To play, just click on a gem, block or an empty space, except
those that touch the edge of the board, if there are gems or blocks
around, they will move according to the following pattern:

      1A2      4B1      3C4
      D*B  ->  A*C  ->  B*D   etc.
      4C3      3D2      2A1

  ...where the '*' symbol represents the position you clicked on,
which can be an empty space, a gem or a block, and 1, 2, 3, 4 and
A, B, C, D represent gems, blocks or empty spaces. The items at the
positions represented by the numbers 1, 2, 3, and 4 will turn
clockwise while items represented by the letters A, B, C, and D
will turn counterclockwise. All gems of the same type that get
placed next to each other (either horizontally or vertically) will
be removed, and the gems or blocks that are located above will fall
in the emptied spaces.

  When gems fall in emptied space, some of them may be next to
similar gems and then will also be removed and so on, this may
cause a chain reaction where in the end only a few gems remain. The
main idea is to try to eliminate all the gems in each game level.

  Score is obtained depending on the number of gems of the same
type that are next to each other, the more there are, the more
points you get!

  At the end of a game level, Gemology will show how many gems that
are left. If one or more gems remain, those gems will be added to
the current number of remaining gems. If that number reach 20, then
the game will be over.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS:

  3 buttons are shown in the game window:

 -Minimize game window: This button indicated by a small triangle
                        icon, is located on the lower left of the
                        window. It minimizes the size of the game
                        window while keeping the same gameboard
                        tile size.
 -About:                Displays the informations about the game.
 -Gems:                 Displays the amount of gems remaining for
                        the current game board.

